intellan.name: intellan

revisions.description: Version 1.4.10 Removed the extra 1 after enterprises ID

intellan.description: The MIB module for Intel LAN SNMP agent.

InterfaceIndex.name: InterfaceIndex
InterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface or interface sub-layer in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

company.name: company
company.description: Company that provided this MIB - Intel(R) Corporation.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of this component - Intel(R) Network Adapter(s), Advanced Management.

operatingSystem.name: operatingSystem
operatingSystem.description: Operating System of the server on which the SNMP agent is executed.

mibVersion1_4_3.name: mibVersion1_4_3
mibVersion1_4_3.description: Version of this MIB - the empty string is always returned.

mibVersionSupported.name: mibVersionSupported
mibVersionSupported.description: Version of the MIB supported by the agent. 1.x.y indicates that every MIB version of that template is supported by the agent.

agentExtensionVersion.name: agentExtensionVersion
agentExtensionVersion.description: Version of the SNMP extension agent.

status.name: status
status.description: Indicates status and functionality of the adapter(s) - whether the base driver and ANS are loaded.

genericAdaptersAttrTable.name: genericAdaptersAttrTable
genericAdaptersAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all kinds of adapters.

genericAdapterAttrEntry.name: genericAdapterAttrEntry
genericAdapterAttrEntry.description: Attributes common to all kinds of adapters. There is one 'entry' for each physical or virtual adapter.

adapterIndex.name: adapterIndex
adapterIndex.description: A unique value, greater than or equal to zero, for each interface.

adapterName.name: adapterName
adapterName.description: Name of the adapter interface. There is a unique name for each instance.

adapterType.name: adapterType
adapterType.description: Type of adapter (member, stand-alone, or virtual).

adapterDriverLoadStatus.name: adapterDriverLoadStatus
adapterDriverLoadStatus.description: Load status of the driver: -'loaded' if the driver is loaded on the NIC; 'notLoaded' otherwise. A status of 'notLoaded' means that the NIC is missing (via 'hotRemove') or the driver is not fully loaded for some reason.

genericAdaptersDriversAttrTable.name: genericAdaptersDriversAttrTable
genericAdaptersDriversAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all kinds of adapter drivers.

genericAdapterDriverAttrEntry.name: genericAdapterDriverAttrEntry
genericAdapterDriverAttrEntry.description: Attributes common to all kinds of adapter drivers. There is one 'entry' for each adapter driver

adapterDriverInfo.name: adapterDriverInfo
adapterDriverInfo.description: Additional information about the adapter. Includes name of the NIC.

adapterDriverDate.name: adapterDriverDate
adapterDriverDate.description: Adapter driver creation date (in mm/dd/yy format).

genericAdaptersTrafficStatsAttrTable.name: genericAdaptersTrafficStatsAttrTable
genericAdaptersTrafficStatsAttrTable.description: Traffic stats common to all kinds of adapters.

genericAdapterTrafficStatsAttrEntry.name: genericAdapterTrafficStatsAttrEntry
genericAdapterTrafficStatsAttrEntry.description: Traffic stats common to all kinds of adapters. There is one 'entry' for each adapter instance.

adapterRxErrors.name: adapterRxErrors
adapterRxErrors.description: Total number of packets received with errors (packets that failed to reach the protocol).

adapterTxErrors.name: adapterTxErrors
adapterTxErrors.description: Total number of packets that failed to transmit.

adapterRxDropped.name: adapterRxDropped
adapterRxDropped.description: Total number of receive packets dropped due to overrun.

adapterTxDropped.name: adapterTxDropped
adapterTxDropped.description: Total number of transmit packets dropped due to successive collisions.

adapterRxMulticast.name: adapterRxMulticast
adapterRxMulticast.description: Total number of Multicast packets received.

physicalAdaptersAttrTable.name: physicalAdaptersAttrTable
physicalAdaptersAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all Physical Adapters.

physicalAdapterAttrEntry.name: physicalAdapterAttrEntry
physicalAdapterAttrEntry.description: Attributes common to all Physical Adapters. There is one 'entry' for each standalone or member adapter.

physicalAdapterIndex.name: physicalAdapterIndex
physicalAdapterIndex.description: A unique value, greater than or equal to zero, for each interface.

physicalAdapterLinkStatus.name: physicalAdapterLinkStatus
physicalAdapterLinkStatus.description: Physical adapter link status. Appears only if available - that is, only if the driver is compliant with SNMP; otherwise, NO_SUCH_NAME is returned.

physicalAdapterLinkStatusChangesCounter.name: physicalAdapterLinkStatusChangesCounter
physicalAdapterLinkStatusChangesCounter.description: Number of changes in physical adapter link status. Any change ('up-to-down' or 'down- to-up') is counted. This value can be reset (to zero) by the user; no other value is permitted. This value appears only if it is available - that is, only if the driver is compliant with SNMP; otherwise, NO_SUCH_NAME is returned.

physicalAdapterSpeed.name: physicalAdapterSpeed
physicalAdapterSpeed.description: Physical adapter speed (in Mbps). Appears only for an SNMP-compliant adapter with link up.

physicalAdapterDplxMode.name: physicalAdapterDplxMode
physicalAdapterDplxMode.description: Physical Adapter Duplex Mode. Appears only for an SNMP-compliant adapter with link up.

physicalAdapterAutoNegotiation.name: physicalAdapterAutoNegotiation
physicalAdapterAutoNegotiation.description: Physical adapter autonegotiation mode. This value appears only if it is available - that is, only if the driver is compliant with SNMP; otherwise, NO_SUCH_NAME is returned.

physicalAdapterCurrentNA.name: physicalAdapterCurrentNA
physicalAdapterCurrentNA.description: Current MAC address of the physical adapter(in hex notation).

physicalAdapterPermanentNA.name: physicalAdapterPermanentNA
physicalAdapterPermanentNA.description: Permanent MAC address of the physical adapter(in hex notation).

physicalAdapterOnlineDiagStatus.name: physicalAdapterOnlineDiagStatus
physicalAdapterOnlineDiagStatus.description: The Online Diagnostics Status of the Physical Adapter. Online Diagnostics consist of Link Test and other Hardware Tests.

physicalAdapterExpressTeamed.name: physicalAdapterExpressTeamed
physicalAdapterExpressTeamed.description: Physical Adapter Express team status. Appears only for an adapter with express teaming capability.

physicalAdapterExpressTeamBundleId.name: physicalAdapterExpressTeamBundleId
physicalAdapterExpressTeamBundleId.description: Unique value to identify the express team in the system.

physicalAdaptersAttrOffloadTable.name: physicalAdaptersAttrOffloadTable
physicalAdaptersAttrOffloadTable.description: Attributes of offloading-enabled physical adapters. There is one 'entry' for each SNMP-compliant physical adapter.

physicalAdapterAttrOffloadEntry.name: physicalAdapterAttrOffloadEntry
physicalAdapterAttrOffloadEntry.description: Attributes of offloading-enabled physical adapters. There is one 'entry' for each SNMP-compliant physical adapter.

physicalAdapterTcpRxChecksumOffLoadEnabl.name: physicalAdapterTcpRxChecksumOffLoadEnable
physicalAdapterTcpRxChecksumOffLoadEnabl.description: When enabled, TCP for 'receive' checksums are performed in hardware.

physicalAdapterTcpTxChecksumOffLoadEnabl.name: physicalAdapterTcpTxChecksumOffLoadEnable
physicalAdapterTcpTxChecksumOffLoadEnabl.description: When enabled, TCP for 'transmit' checksums are performed in hardware.

physicalAdapterIpv4RxChecksumOffLoadEnab.name: physicalAdapterIpv4RxChecksumOffLoadEnable
physicalAdapterIpv4RxChecksumOffLoadEnab.description: When enabled, IPv4 for 'receive' checksums are performed in hardware.

physicalAdapterIpv4TxChecksumOffLoadEnab.name: physicalAdapterIpv4TxChecksumOffLoadEnable
physicalAdapterIpv4TxChecksumOffLoadEnab.description: When enabled, IPv4 for 'receive' checksums are performed in hardware.

physicalAdapterIpv4TCPSegmentationOffLoa.name: physicalAdapterIpv4TCPSegmentationOffLoadEnable
physicalAdapterIpv4TCPSegmentationOffLoa.description: When enabled, TCP Segmentation is performed in hardware.

virtualAdaptersAttrTable.name: virtualAdaptersAttrTable
virtualAdaptersAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all iANS-virtual adapters.

virtualAdapterAttrEntry.name: virtualAdapterAttrEntry
virtualAdapterAttrEntry.description: Attributes common to all iANS-virtual adapters. There is one 'entry' for each virtual adapter

virtualAdapterIndex.name: virtualAdapterIndex
virtualAdapterIndex.description: A unique value, greater than or equal to zero, for each interface.

virtualAdapterAnsId.name: virtualAdapterAnsId
virtualAdapterAnsId.description: ID of the team to which the adapter belongs.

virtualAdaptersVlanAttrTable.name: virtualAdaptersVlanAttrTable
virtualAdaptersVlanAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all iANS-virtual adapters VLANs.

virtualAdapterVlanAttrEntry.name: virtualAdapterVlanAttrEntry
virtualAdapterVlanAttrEntry.description: VLAN attributes.Appears for virtual adapters that support VLANs only. There is one 'entry' for each VLAN.

virtualAdapterVlanId.name: virtualAdapterVlanId
virtualAdapterVlanId.description: ID for this virtual adapter VLAN.

ansAttrEntry.name: ansAttrEntry
ansAttrEntry.description: ANS attributes. There is one 'entry' for each team

ansNumberOfMembers.name: ansNumberOfMembers
ansNumberOfMembers.description: Number of member adapters in the team.

ansNumberOfVirtualAdapters.name: ansNumberOfVirtualAdapters
ansNumberOfVirtualAdapters.description: Number of virtual adapters in the team.

ansVlanAttrEntry.name: ansVlanAttrEntry
ansVlanAttrEntry.description: ANS VLAN attributes. Appears only if VLAN is active. There is one 'entry' for each Vlan.

ansVlanTaggingType.name: ansVlanTaggingType
ansVlanTaggingType.description: Tagging type of the VLAN adapter.

ansTeamAttrEntry.name: ansTeamAttrEntry
ansTeamAttrEntry.description: ANS team attributes. Appears only when adapter teaming exist. There is one 'entry' for each team.

ansTeamLinkState.name: ansTeamLinkState
ansTeamLinkState.description: Team link state. Aggregation of the link state of all team members ( 0 = some up).

ansTeamSpeed.name: ansTeamSpeed
ansTeamSpeed.description: Team speed.Speed of the current primary member (in Mbps).

ansTeamProbesState.name: ansTeamProbesState
ansTeamProbesState.description: If enabled, the ANS uses probes to check on its members.

ansTeamLoadBalanceRefresh.name: ansTeamLoadBalanceRefresh
ansTeamLoadBalanceRefresh.description: In seconds. If available, the number of seconds that passes before the software resets or refreshes the current load across team members.

ansTeamProbesSendTime.name: ansTeamProbesSendTime
ansTeamProbesSendTime.description: In seconds. If available, the interval in seconds during which probe packets are sent.

ansTeamPreferredPrimaryIndex.name: ansTeamPreferredPrimaryIndex
ansTeamPreferredPrimaryIndex.description: Index of the preferred primary member adapter.

ansTeamCurrentPrimaryIndex.name: ansTeamCurrentPrimaryIndex
ansTeamCurrentPrimaryIndex.description: Index of the current primary member adapter.

ansTeamPreviousPrimaryIndex.name: ansTeamPreviousPrimaryIndex
ansTeamPreviousPrimaryIndex.description: Index of the previous primary member adapter.

ansTeamFailoverCounter.name: ansTeamFailoverCounter
ansTeamFailoverCounter.description: Failover counter - that is, the number of failovers the team suffered. This value can be reset by the user - that is, it can be set to zero only; no other value is permitted.

ansTeamSlaCompatible.name: ansTeamSlaCompatible
ansTeamSlaCompatible.description: Indicates compatibility with Static Link Aggregation mode when in IEEE 802.3AD mode.

ansTeamAggrSelectionMode.name: ansTeamAggrSelectionMode
ansTeamAggrSelectionMode.description: Indicates aggregation selection mode when in IEEE 802.3AD mode.

ansTeamRlbSupport.name: ansTeamRlbSupport
ansTeamRlbSupport.description: Indicates whether 'receive load balancing support' is enabled when in AdaptiveLoadBalancing teaming mode. (If disabled, only the transmission is balanced.)

ansMembersAttrTable.name: ansMembersAttrTable
ansMembersAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all iANS-TeamMember Adapters.

ansMemberAttrEntry.name: ansMemberAttrEntry
ansMemberAttrEntry.description: Attributes common to all iANS-TeamMember Adapters. There is one 'entry' for each team member adapter.

ansMemberIndex.name: ansMemberIndex
ansMemberIndex.description: A unique value for each member. The value is non-negative and identical to the value of the physical adapter associated with this member.

ansMemberAnsId.name: ansMemberAnsId
ansMemberAnsId.description: ID of the ANS to which the Adapter belongs.

ansTeamMembersAttrTable.name: ansTeamMembersAttrTable
ansTeamMembersAttrTable.description: Attributes common to all iANS-TeamMember Adapters.

ansTeamMemberAttrEntry.name: ansTeamMemberAttrEntry
ansTeamMemberAttrEntry.description: Attributes of iANS-TeamMember Adapters related to adapter teaming. Appears only if adapter teaming exists.

ansTeamMemberFailureCounter.name: ansTeamMemberFailureCounter
ansTeamMemberFailureCounter.description: Failure counter - that is, the number of failovers from this member. This value can be reset by the user - that is, it can be set to zero only; no other value is permitted.

physicalAdapterLinkUpTrap.name: physicalAdapterLinkUpTrap
physicalAdapterLinkUpTrap.description: Adapter has reached a linkup state.

physicalAdapterLinkDownTrap.name: physicalAdapterLinkDownTrap
physicalAdapterLinkDownTrap.description: Adapter has reached a link down state.

physicalAdapterOnlineDiagFailedTrap.name: physicalAdapterOnlineDiagFailedTrap
physicalAdapterOnlineDiagFailedTrap.description: Adapter's online diagnostics failed. Online diagnostics might fail because of link loss or other hardware issues.

physicalAdapterLinkUpDownTrapEnable.name: physicalAdapterLinkUpDownTrapEnable
physicalAdapterLinkUpDownTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether a physical adapter's link up and link down traps are enabled. The user can set this value.

physicalAdapterAddedRemovedTrapEnable.name: physicalAdapterAddedRemovedTrapEnable
physicalAdapterAddedRemovedTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether a physical adapter's 'added' and 'removed' traps are enabled. The user can set this value.

physicalAdapterOnlineDiagPassedFailedTra.name: physicalAdapterOnlineDiagPassedFailedTrapEnable
physicalAdapterOnlineDiagPassedFailedTra.description: Indicates whether physicalAdapterOnlineDiag 'passed' and 'failed' are enabled.

virtualAdapterAddedTrap.name: virtualAdapterAddedTrap
virtualAdapterAddedTrap.description: Virtual adapter has been added to a team.

virtualAdapterRemovedTrap.name: virtualAdapterRemovedTrap
virtualAdapterRemovedTrap.description: Virtual adapter has been removed from a team.

virtualAdaptersTrapEnable.name: virtualAdaptersTrapEnable
virtualAdaptersTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether virtual adapter traps are enabled. The user can set this value.

ansTeamFailoverTrap.name: ansTeamFailoverTrap
ansTeamFailoverTrap.description: The primary team member has been changed.

ansTrapEnable.name: ansTrapEnable
ansTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether team traps are enabled. The user can set this value.

teamMemberAddedTrap.name: teamMemberAddedTrap
teamMemberAddedTrap.description: Member has been added to a team.

teamMemberRemovedTrap.name: teamMemberRemovedTrap
teamMemberRemovedTrap.description: Member has been removed from a team.

teamMemberTrapEnable.name: teamMemberTrapEnable
teamMemberTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether traps for members are enabled. The user can set this value.

intellan_compliance.description: Compliance statements for the Intel Lan Agent.
